target.comment:
1. Comprehensive PCB inventory for in-service equipment, waste stockpiles and contaminated sites to be maintained on an on-going basis;
2. High concentration PCB wastes as priority hazardous wastes in national waste management legislation/regulations is explicitly reflected and is consistent with applicable international standards and the basel Convention on trans-boundary movement of hazardous waste;
3. Technical capacity and operational plans in place for the management of PCBs on a long term basis including a designated national lab. facility;
4. Major holders have secure storage facilities.

